  "$id": "https://aureline.dev/schemas/companion/implement-runbook-execution-rows-deviation-notes-export-bundles-and-browser-or-vendor-console-handoff-truth.schema.json",
  "title": "Aureline runbook execution rows, deviation notes, export bundles, and browser or vendor-console handoff",
  "description": "Export-safe packet for the runbook execution phase of an incident: the per-step execution rows that record each runbook step as it runs, the first-class deviation notes that record every departure from the runbook, the export bundles that package an incident's transcript and evidence for sharing, and the browser or vendor-console handoff that resumes an item in an external surface. It projects four sections — execution_row, deviation_note, export_bundle, and external_handoff — each inheriting qualification from the frozen M5 companion-matrix incident_workspace lane, and gives every item an exact desktop handoff. Read-mostly and attributable: every section is read-only, an execution row never applies an automated step without explicit host approval, and a row or note that loses attribution narrows to unattributed rather than claiming a provenance it cannot prove; every deviation is recorded as a first-class note. Local-first external handoff: a browser or vendor-console handoff always discloses that it requires provider continuity and always keeps an exact desktop handoff as the local-first fallback, so the local core never depends on the external surface. Stale-state honesty: every item carries a freshness state, stale or unknown freshness is always labeled, an incomplete export bundle is labeled, and a degraded item is never shown as live. Degraded state (relay unavailable, stale proof, inactive host, narrowed trust, lost incident attribution, incomplete export, unreachable external console, narrowed upstream lane, unresolved handoff, downgraded freshness) is labeled rather than hidden. Credential bodies, raw provider payloads, and raw execution, note, bundle, or vendor-console bodies never cross this boundary.",
